	note = {Perhaps the first quantative study of overwintering sites in California. Most papers cite this article when describing overwintering habitat and monarchs. The authors did mark and recapture studies at three prominent sites in California, one of which is Ellwood Main, a grove I have worked on extensively. They found that there was high site fidelity with monarchs, which was previously unknown before this paper. There are many interesting anecodtal descriptions of behavior in the grove, but only a few quantitative studies. They do no mention microclimate parameters, except a speculation that monarchs will roost just above the cold night air.},
